scene.message:
Nanjo: Indeed, it's prettier{nl}
now than when I gave the{nl}
freshman rep's speech at{nl}
the entrance ceremony.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Wish this place were{nl}
bigger~ It's way too cramped{nl}
for my stage!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: What're you trying{nl}
to do, coming all the way{nl}
to the stage? We're supposed{nl}
to go get checked out, right?{waitkey}{ret}

Student: All kinds of things{nl}
happened on this old stage.{waitkey}Over its long history, sweat{nl}
and tears — and blood — have{nl}
all been shed upon it.{waitkey}Even if the stage is gone,{nl}
the feelings of those who{nl}
stood on it won't vanish{nl}
so easily...{waitkey}So, how's my line? It's long,{nl}
so it was a pain to memorize.{waitkey}{ret}

Student: At last, the time{nl}
has come. The time when the{nl}
old feelings within this{nl}
stage are set free...{waitkey}Just kidding{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Good line, huh? I wrote the{nl}
script myself.{waitkey}{ret}
